29/07/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police have detained 137 illegal immigrants who were allegedly trying to sail to the Greek island of Samos. The would-be immigrants from Azerbaijan, Mauritania, Algeria, Afghanistan and Somalia were found aboard a Turkish fishing vessel Wednesday (28 July). Three Turks were also arrested. Authorities are searching for the captain of the vessel and several crewmembers who managed to escape. (AFP - 28/07/04)
